  "texts": [
    "The inherent abilities of chatbots to handle yes/no questions efficiently and without misinterpretation make them particularly valuable in this context, minimising human error and optimising the data collection process.",
    "Several studies have highlighted that chatbots provide a more engaging patient interaction, often perceived as less intimidating than traditional face-to-face conversations [27], [48].",
    "This interaction is crucial as it motivates patients to disclose more comprehensive health information, which can lead to better health outcomes.",
    "However, they may underperform in scenarios requiring nuanced understanding and empathy.",
    "Studies have discussed that face-to-face communication is necessary to build trust when talking about more sensitive issues [42]."
